Title: Toyota Programming Contest  2025（AtCoder Beginner Contest 389)
Name: Square Price
Problem Statement:
There are N types of products, each having 10^{100} units in stock.
You can buy any non-negative number of units of each product. To buy k units of the i-th product, it costs k^2 P_i yen.
If your total purchase cost is at most M yen, what is the maximum number of units you can buy in total?
IO Styles:
Input
The input is given from Standard Input in the following format:
N M
P_1 ... P_N
Output
Print the answer.

Sample Detail.explanation: If you buy one unit of the 1st product and two units of the 2nd product, the total purchase cost is 1^2 \times 4 + 2^2 \times 1 = 8. It is impossible to buy four or more units in total with a total cost of at most 9 yen, so the answer is 3.
